        h3 Alternative Names
        p
          b Generic Names:
          |  flecainide (fle-KAY-nide)
        p
          b Brand Names:
          |  Tambocor
        hr

        h3 Uses
        li
          | Treating and preventing various types of irregular heartbeat that can be life threatening
        li
          | Stabilizing the heart rhythm when the heart is beating too fast or in an irregular rhythm
        hr

        h3 Dosage
        li
          b Adult Dose for Ventricular Tachycardia:
          br
          |  Initially 100 mg orally every 12 hours, may be increased 50 mg per day, MAX 400 mg/day
          br
          br
        li
          b Adult Dose for Atrial Fibrillation:
          br
          |  Initially 50 mg orally every 12 hours. may be increased 50 mg per day
          br
          br
        li
          b Adult Dose for Wolff-Parkinson-White Syndrome:
          br
          |  Initially 50 mg orally every 12 hours, may be increased 50 mg per day, MAX 400 mg/day
          br
          br
        li
          b Adult Dose for Paroxysmal Supraventricular Tachycardia
          br
          |  Initially 50 mg orally every 12 hours. may be increased 50 mg per day
          br
          br
        li
          b Pediatric Dose for Supraventricular Tachycardia
          br
          |  <1 month: Initially 2 mg/kg/day orally divided every 12 hours. may be increased 50 mg per day
          br
          |  >1 month: Initially 1 to 3 mg/kg/day orally or 50 to 100 mg/m2/day orally in 3 divided dose
          br
          br
        
